		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Augusta Ga.</placeName> <date>28<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. Novr. 5626</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Revd. I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Yours of the <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> reached me<lb/> yesterday.  I mentioned in my last that the current<lb/> Nos. of the Occident which I had ordered&#44; had come<lb/> to hand.  I have obtained another subscriber.<lb/>  <persName>Mr L. Loeser</persName> of this city&#44; in whom please mail<lb/> the Magazine.  As soon as one or two Nos. reach<lb/> the parties&#44; I will make the necessary collection.  You<lb/> wish as in the extension of circulation in the country<lb/> parts shall receive due attention&#59; and as I sometimes<lb/> travel to and for as <add>Hebrew</add> and <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; I will take <del>&#63;</del><lb/> advantage of such occasions to advance its interests.<lb/>  Be assured of my sincere willingness to do what I can<lb/> for you&#44; and in this annexion<add>&#63;</add> let me add&#44; that my<lb/> advocacy of the Occident is unfettered as I have<lb/> undertaken the agency of no other paper or periodical.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have checked the incipient<lb/> Reform tendency&#44; which made itself apparent in the<lb/> semi&#45;official request of the Board of Trustees to use</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>the &#40;Sunday School&#41; Melodeon together with some of<lb/> the <placeName>Hazel St.</placeName> Syngue hymns on <date>Thanksgiving Day</date>.  I<lb/> refused instante<add>&#63;</add>&#44; &#38; have probably given cause for some<lb/> ill will in consequence&#59; but this is nothing new&#44; as I<lb/> was <sic>martyrized</sic> by <persName>Col <sic>Jacobs&#39;s</sic></persName> clique in <placeName>Charleston</placeName><lb/> for my <del>pass</del> opposition to their wiles and intrigues<lb/> when they tried to use me for their purposes.  They<lb/> never forgave my non&#45;endorsation of <persName>Mr. Harris</persName>.  It<lb/> was attempted to argue here the perfect legality of<lb/> playing on a musical instrument on a day that was<lb/> neither <date>Sabbath</date> nor Festival&#44; but this I would not<lb/> discuss&#44; as to my mind it was not the true point&#44;<lb/> as I wished to guard against the entering wedge.<lb/>  So whilst I remain here&#44; and how long I may do<lb/> so is uncertain as the field dog not altogether<lb/> suit me&#44;&#8212;&#8220;they hybrid&#8221; has received its quietus of<lb/> course&#59; all this is entre nous.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Can you not brush up our people<lb/> in <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>&#63;  My family letters from <placeName>Kingston</placeName> depict<lb/> religion as in a state of decadence.  The English &#38;<lb/> German Synagogue&#44; will a model Congr&#8212;has an almost<lb/> nominal attendance on <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; late and sparse&#44; &#38;<lb/> on <date>Sunday</date> evenings so hopeless is the attainment of</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add> that the Schule is not opened.  Of the Portuguese<lb/> Congr I hear nothing&#59; but <hi rend="underline">former</hi> advices lead me to<lb/> infer that that is little&#44; if at all&#44; better in this<lb/> respect.  Alas&#33; How are the mighty fallen&#33;  Our<lb/> friend <persName>M N Nathan</persName> should have taken the helm<lb/> again&#44; for if aught could be done&#44; he is the man<lb/> to do it.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr Jacobs</persName> reciprocates your kind<lb/> remembrance&#44; and with much regard</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Believe me</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Henry S. Jacobs</persName>.</p>
		</body>
